    <tr>
      <td width="38" height="36"></td>
      <td width="110" height="36" align="middle"><b><A class=Sublink href="#Buy"><font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="3">How
        to purchase</font></a></b></td>
      <td width="420" height="36" class="Mainlink"><font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="2">Our
        pages are divided into Sections - Categories and Products. Start by
        selecting a section from the column on the left hand side of the screen.
        Categories for that Section will be displayed on the central main
        screen. The section title will be displayed at the top of that central
        screen. Now browse down through the categories and then select a
        category. The categories will be replaced with a list of products for
        that category.</font>
        <p><font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="2">Choose
        a product by clicking on the product description. The central page will
        be replaced by a full detailed description of the product. A picture of
        the item (If available) will be displayed below the pricing information
        of the product. Clicking on the picture will take you directly to the
        web page of the supplier of that product (If available) and hopefully
        provide you with further information on the product.</font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="2">To
        buy the item, (Add it to your shopping basket, as is usually displayed)
        simply enter the number of that product that you require (<font color="#0000ff">Order
        Qty</font>). Then click the button called <font color="#0000ff">Update
        Order</font>. On clicking the button, your current order status will be
        displayed. Please note, until you click the <font color="#0000ff">BUY</font>
        button, you have not as yet placed the order. Some products will come
        with <font color="#0000ff">optional extras</font>.&nbsp; These <font color="#0000ff">Optional
        Extras</font> will be displayed in a drop down box/s somewhere near the
        quantity entry box. Some of the Optional Extras include an additional
        charge which will be displayed next to each item in the list. In other
        cases there is no additional charge but we may require specific
        information regarding size and color etc. Please be careful in selecting
        the correct sizes, specifications etc.</font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="2">If
        you want to specify additional items, use the Back button to take you
        back step by step or click the section list again to reload the product
        Categories for that section.</font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="2">Once
        you are satisfied with your order, click the <font color="#0000ff">Buy </font>button
        at the top of the screen. If you have logged onto our site for the first
        time, you will see a few entry boxes which require information from you
        before you can proceed. Complete the information required and select the
        option to proceed with the purchase. If there is any invalid or unknown
        data, you will be requested to change this until the system is satisfied
        that it has the correct data to continue. Your details will be stored on
        your computer so that the next time you log on, the data can be
        retrieved and automatically displayed for your convenience. Please note.
        We use SSL for all of our Credit card transactions. this ensures that
        your details cannot be read by unscrupulous people.</font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="2">Once
        your order has been processed by the system it is in our hands. We will
        notify you 1) Confirmation of receipt of the order and the details, as
        well as any delivery detail options that may have changed.</font></p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
